Robinson Crusoe;;1997;;PG-13;;Adventure,Drama;;6.0;;Rod Hardy,George Miller;;Pierce Brosnan,William Takaku,Polly Walker,Ian Hart,James Frain,Damian Lewis,Ben Robertson,Martin Grace,Sean Brosnan,Lysette Anthony,Tim McMullan,Mal Tobias,Jim Clark;;Robinson Crusoe flees Britain on a ship after killing his friend over the love of Mary. A fierce ocean storm wrecks his ship and leaves him stranded by himself on an uncharted island. Left to fend for himself, Crusoe seeks out a tentative survival on the island, until he meets Friday, a tribesman whom he saves from being sacrificed. Initially, Crusoe is thrilled to finally have a friend, but he has to defend himself against the tribe who uses the island to sacrifice tribesmen to their gods. Over time, their relationship changes from master-slave to a mutual respected friendship despite their difference in culture and religion.;;https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0117496/